div.p:
                        I. 5. 
                        What a reproachful thing, is Univerſal imitation of the beſt men! Their holy Faith and Life is all you are bid to follow. To Swallow their Errors, and practiſe their Sins, is what God and they themſelves forbid you. And is imitating or them in the things wherein they were not themſelves. But were more Satan's, than their own men. Wherefore ſo to do is to comply with Satan, not to conform unto them. Let it alſo be conſidered;

that to affect and ſtrain to take up their (unaffected) Tones, Geſtures, Garbs, &c. is to but ape their Humanity it ſelf. And nothing of an imitation of their Piety. In Children it is playfulneſs; in Men it's Childiſhneſs, if no worſe.
